---
description: Enforce absolute internal imports via #/ alias
alwaysApply: true
---

# Internal Imports

- Use absolute internal imports with `#/...` for project code.
- Do not introduce relative imports (`./`, `../`) between internal modules when `#/...` is possible.
- For tests, use package test aliases (`#/tests/...`) when available.

## Allowed exception

- Relative imports are allowed only when the target is outside alias-mapped roots
  (`src/**`, `tests/**`) or when no `#/...` alias exists for that path.

## Alias naming convention

- Preferred test alias key: `#/tests/*` (plural).
- Keep `package.json` `imports` and `tsconfig.json` `paths` aligned for the same alias keys.

## Refactor rule

- When moving files, normalize imports to `#/...` immediately.
- Avoid mixed alias styles like `#/test/*` vs `#/tests/*` in the same package.
